body_html:
FYI it looks like the MacOS CPU Tests are failing because of a grappler issue, and the Windows Cmake Tests are failing because of a failure in tensorflow/python/training/coordinator_test.py. Both of these are unrelated to this PR.

I don't know whether our policy is to always wait for passing tests, or whether we make one-off exceptions. FWIW this PR is only changing a VLOG(1) to VLOG(3), and should be safe to merge, despite the unrelated test failures.

FYI it looks like the `MacOS CPU Tests` are failing because of a grappler issue, and the `Windows Cmake Tests` are failing because of a failure in `tensorflow/python/training/coordinator_test.py`.  Both of these are unrelated to this PR.

I don't know whether our policy is to always wait for passing tests, or whether we make one-off exceptions.  FWIW this PR is only changing a `VLOG(1)` to `VLOG(3)`, and should be safe to merge, despite the unrelated test failures.
